meanings: (원래 상태로) return (to), be restored (to), go[get] back (to), revert to (=되돌아가다)
(길을 우회해서) make[take] a detour, take a roundabout way
실용회화-입국심사대 Do you have a return airplane ticket?

meanings.meaning: Dust thou art, and unto dust shalt thou return.

examples.korean: His life seemed stuck in limbo; he could not go forward and he could not go back. 발음듣기 그의 삶은 이도 저도 아닌 상태에 갇혀 있는 것 같았다. 그는 앞으로 나아갈 수도 없고 뒤로 돌아갈 수도 없었다. Oxford Advanced Learner's English-Korean Dictionary
examples.english: His life seemed stuck in limbo; he could not go forward and he could not go back. 발음

examples.korean: Could you go back to the beginning of the story? 발음듣기 그 이야기의 처음으로 다시 돌아갈 수 있어요? Oxford Advanced Learner's English-Korean Dictionary
examples.english: Could you go back to the beginning of the story? 발음

examples.korean: They watered down the soup to make it go further. 발음듣기 그들은 더 많은 사람들에게 돌아갈 수 있도록 수프에 물을 탔다. Oxford Advanced Learner's English-Korean Dictionary
examples.english: They watered down the soup to make it go further. 발음

examples.korean: She was happy apart from the fact that she could not return home. 발음듣기 그녀는 집으로 돌아갈 수 없다는 점 외에는 행복했다. Oxford Advanced Learner's English-Korean Dictionary
examples.english: She was happy apart from the fact that she could not return home. 발음

examples.korean: They are hoping for a return to normality now that the war is over. 발음듣기 이제 전쟁이 끝났으니 그들은 정상 상태로 돌아갈 것을 희망하고 있다. Oxford Advanced Learner's English-Korean Dictionary
examples.english: They are hoping for a return to normality now that the war is over. 발음
